  "texts": [
    "This is in contrast to the perspective presented in [4,25].• We show that, in this alternative perspective, the bulk theory has a rigid radial symmetry and a candidate for the \"secret representations\" of [4] naturally arises.The structure of this paper is as follows: in section 2 we review and motivate aspects of the k = 1 string from first principles and review the connection with the hybrid formalism.",
    "The interpretation of the target space is discussed, including connections to the bulk twistor theory and the ambitwistor space of the boundary theory.",
    "We introduce an alternative target space interpretation of the theory that makes the connection with the non-linear sigma model of AdS 3 more transparent.",
    "Section 3 reviews the construction of correlation functions in the k = 1 string.",
    "This section does not contain any novel material per se, but presents 2 Strings on AdS 3 at k = 1The hybrid formalism of [23,30,31] can be applied to study the minimal tension k = 1 string on AdS 3 × S 3 × M 4, where M 4 can be either T 4 or K3."
